      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/11/85",
      "text": [
        " : قُلْتُ لِأَبِي عَبْدِ اَللَّهِ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ اَلرَّجُلُ يَشْتَرِي مِنَ اَلرَّجُلِ اَلْبَيْعَ فَيَسْتَوْهِبُهُ بَعْدَ اَلشِّرَاءِ مِنْ غَيْرِ أَنْ يَحْمِلَهُ عَلَى اَلْكُرْهِ قَالَ \"لاَ بَأْسَ بِهِ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3856 - It is narrated from Yunus bin Ya'qub who said: I said to Abu Abdillah (as), \"A man purchases goods from another man and then asks for them as a gift after the purchase, without compelling him.\"\nImam (as) said: \"There is no harm in it.\""
        ]
      }
    },
